<HEAD>Eds: SUBS the TITUSVILLE, Pa.-dated Nelson item to restore dropped
word `attack' in lead.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>Tim Nelson</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TITUSVILLE, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tim Nelson, 53, a retired WTIV radio
announcer and Titusville Area Chamber of Commerce President, died
Saturday of a heart attack.
   Nelson worked for WTIV for 29 years, beginning in 1955. He was a
station announcer and also served as program director. Nelson left
the station in 1980 to work for the chamber.
   Nelson was a member of a number of community organizations,
including the Titusville Kiwanis Club and the Pennsylvania Chamber
of Commerce Executives.
   He is survived by his wife, Dorothy, and four daughters.
</TEXT>
