<FIRST>r a PM-BoxOffice     12-19 0434</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Box Office,0453</SECOND>
<HEAD>`Christmas Vacation' No. 1 at the Movies</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MICHAEL FLEEMAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``National Lampoon's Christmas Vacation'' was
the nation's No. 1 movie last weekend, displacing the dark comedy
``The War of the Roses.''
   ``She-Devil,'' teaming TV's Roseanne Barr and Oscar winner Meryl
Streep, fell from fourth to out of the Top 10, and the Eddie
Murphy-Richard Pryor collaboration ``Harlem Nights'' dropped from
sixth to 10th place.
   Warner Bros.' ``Christmas Vacation,'' starring Chevy Chase,
moved up from second on a $7.23 million return last weekend while
``The War of the Roses,'' with Kathleen Turner and Michael Douglas
as dueling spouses, slipped to No. 2.
   ``Back to the Future Part II'' was third. The film has collected
$75.5 million since Thanksgiving weekend.
   Disney's animated feature ``The Little Mermaid'' was fourth and
``The Wizard,'' starring TV's young Fred Savage as a video game
whiz, opened at No. 5.
   ``Family Business,'' starring Dustin Hoffman, Sean Connery and
Matthew Broderick, had a disappointing debut, earning $2.1 million
and finishing sixth.
   Finishing seventh was the all-star ensemble ``Steel Magnolias,''
and the pairing of two other big stars, Robert DeNiro and Sean
Penn, produced an eighth-place debut for ``We're No Angels.''
   The Paul Newman-starring ``Blaze,'' the story of Louisiana Gov.
Earl Long's love affair with stripper Blaze Starr, opened at No. 9
with $1.7 million.
   Joining ``She-Devil'' in the drop from the Top 10 were ``Look
Who's Talking,'' ``Prancer'' and ``All Dogs Go to Heaven.''
   Here are the top movie ticket sales for the weekend as tallied
by Entertainment Data and Exhibitor Relations Inc.
   1. ``National Lampoon's Christmas Vacation,'' Warner Bros.,
$7.23 million weekend gross, 1,950 screens, $3,709 per screen,
$33.64 million total gross, three weeks in release.
   2. ``The War of the Roses,'' 20th Century Fox, $6.98 million,
1,395 screens, $5,000 per screen, $19.18 million, two weeks.
   3. ``Back to the Future Part II,'' Universal, $4.41 million,
2,023 screens, $2,180 per screen, $75.54 million, three weeks.
   4. ``The Little Mermaid,'' Disney, $2.52 million, 1,249 screens,
$2,019 per screen, $28.94 million, five weeks.
   5. ``The Wizard,'' Universal, $2.14 million, 1,155 screens,
$1,855 per screen, $2.14 million, one week.
   6. ``Family Business,'' Tri-Star, $2.13 million, 1,201 screens,
$1,773 per screen, $2.13 million, one week.
   7. ``Steel Magnolias,'' Tri-Star, $2.09 million, 1,102 screens,
$1,900 per screen, $30.7 million, five weeks.
   8. ``We're No Angels,'' Paramount, $2.05 million, 1,239 screens,
$1,652 per screen, $2.05 million, one week.
   9. ``Blaze,'' Disney, $1.74 million, 909 screens, $1,913 per
screen, $1.74 million, one week.
   10. ``Harlem Nights,'' Paramount, $1.72 million, 1,324 screens,
$1,302 per screen, $49.48 million, five weeks.
</TEXT>
