Ward Lay, chairman of the Cotton Bowl Parade Pageantry Committee.
``We just happen to be the parade that has the most beautiful women
in it, but we also just happen to be in the city that has the most
beautiful women in it, and the state, too.''
   ``If they're upset, I'm indeed sorry,'' Lay said. ``But the
parade will go on in its form and not be changed.''
